- VSCode Version: 1.5.0-insider (3d9622208b2167921b6664e04fd1fbd51507a4a0)
- OS Version: Windows 10 Redstone 1

How are sorted the items in the menu? I would like to put item before or after `copy`, `copy path`, `rename` and `delete`.
### Case 1. `"group": "navigation"`

``` json
"menus": {
  "explorer/context": [{
    "command": "duplicate.execute",
    "group": "navigation"
  }]
}
```

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7034281/17830045/7710f36c-66c9-11e6-94ef-0962454b480b.png)
### Case 2. `"group": "1_modification"`

> This group comes next and contains commands that modify your code.

``` json
"menus": {
  "explorer/context": [{
    "command": "duplicate.execute",
    "group": "1_modification"
  }]
}
```

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7034281/17830055/9f6fbfd2-66c9-11e6-9b31-df046957634b.png)
### Case 3. `"group": "9_cutcopypaste"`

> The last default group with the basic editing commands.

``` json
"menus": {
  "explorer/context": [{
    "command": "duplicate.execute",
    "group": "9_cutcopypaste"
  }]
}
```

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7034281/17830059/b9853fc8-66c9-11e6-9a58-ddd957367855.png)

Also in the documentation there is no information that there are groups except `navigation` (https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/extensionAPI/extension-points#_contributesmenus).

